article.headline: Iona 68, Vermont 56
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) -- Steve Burtt scored 17 of his 25 points in the second half to lead unbeaten Iona to a 68-56 victory over Vermont on Sunday. Kiril Wachsman added 10 points and 10 rebounds, and Ricky Soliver added 10 points for the Gaels (5-0), who were playing their first home game after four away games. Mike Trimboli scored 14 points, Martin Klimes added 12 and Kyle Cieplicki 11 for the Catamounts (2-4). Wachsman scored all of his points in the first half to help lead Iona to a 30-29 lead at the break. Vermont hit five three-point goals and shot 57.9 percent from the field in the half, while Iona shot 33.3 percent. Klimes scored the first basket of the second half to give the Catamounts a 31-20 lead. Gary Springer capped a 14-5 scoring run that propelled the Gaels to a 44-36 lead with 10:33 left. Iona led by as much as 58-44 after Burtt, who shot 12-for-15 from the line, hit two free throws with 5:33 left. The Gaels outshot Vermont 46.2 percent to 41.7 percent in the second half and outrebounded the Catamounts 40-26 overall.
